    "name": "ucf_bracket_narrow",
    "description": "2-scenario binary-search probe to narrow the UCF reversal threshold from (0.35, 0.65) established by ucf_threshold_probe.\nKNOWN BOUNDS (cumulative): - ucf=0.20, split=0.50 \u2192 v27 wins  (ucf_threshold_probe sweep_0000) - ucf=0.35, split=0.50 \u2192 v27 wins  (ucf_threshold_probe sweep_0001) - ucf=0.65, split=0.50 \u2192 v26 wins  (user_weight_mini_test sweep_0002, reversal)\nThreshold is in (0.35, 0.65). This probe places two points to tighten the bracket: - ucf=0.50 (binary midpoint): splits the interval in half - ucf=0.57 (upper-range probe): tests whether the threshold is near the high end\nDECISION TABLE:\n  ucf=0.50   ucf=0.57   \u2192 interpretation\n  v27 wins   v27 wins   \u2192 threshold \u2208 (0.57, 0.65) \u2014 pinned near upper bound\n  v27 wins   v26 wins   \u2192 threshold \u2208 (0.50, 0.57) \u2014 well-bounded, reportable\n  v26 wins   v26 wins   \u2192 threshold \u2208 (0.35, 0.50) \u2014 midpoint or below (second point redundant)\n\nuser_split fixed at 0.50 (neutral) \u2014 adversarial dilution case, same as all prior probes. All other parameters identical to ucf_threshold_probe for direct comparability.\nRUNTIME: 1 namespace, ~7.2 hours sequential (2 \u00d7 3.6 hrs). NOTE: ucf=0.50 is a grid member of user_weight_threshold.yaml; results feed directly into the full 30-scenario run.\n",
